      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, the safety net can indeed act as a cushion, allowing individuals to retrain and seek better employment opportunities. This perspective emphasizes that a robust social safety net can provide the necessary support for people to invest in their education and skills, ultimately leading to more stable and higher-paying jobs. It argues that without such a safety net, individuals might be forced to accept suboptimal employment due to immediate financial pressures, thus perpetuating a cycle of low-wage work and economic instability. This view advocates for a balanced approach where the safety net not only supports those in need but also empowers them to achieve long-term economic security and self-sufficiency.",
      "source": "target",
